Jeff Miler,

The matplotlib commands in the current version of Cantera
are for the syntax of a previous version of matplotlib (pre 0.65).  If
you
are using any version from any more recent version, you probably need
to 
replace the command:
&quot;from matplotlib.matlab import *&quot;
to
&quot;from pylab import *&quot;
I think matplotlib comes with a utility to update python programs
to the new syntax.

More can be found in:
http://matplotlib.sourceforge.net/whats_new.html

You might also have difficulties plotting from within
an integrated development environment and/or from
the python command line.
More info can be found at:
http://matplotlib.sourceforge.net/backends.html

On windows (I have the enthought edition of python installed), 
I use the &quot;GTKAgg&quot; backend by executing the commands:
&quot;import matplotlib&quot;
matplotlib.use(&quot;GTKAgg&quot;)

before importing pylab
which seems to work most of the time in &quot;pythonwin&quot; and &quot;idle&quot;.

The command &quot;pylab.ion()&quot; might also be useful which turns the
interactive mode of matplotlib on.

Dave H.


